fields.description:
I have added Custom Domain for my bitbucket repository.\\
But when I go to My repository&#x27;s Overview page and click &#x27;Clone&#x27; button I&#x27;m getting link like

{code}
git clone git@bitbucket.org:username/project.git
{code}

instead of

{code}
git clone git@git.mycustomdomain.com:username/project.git
{code}

I used to have a {{test}} Git bucket. I deleted it and create a new one with mercurial and same name.

The repo never get created, it always says: {{Please wait a moment while we create your repository.}}

I have 2 repo stuck the same way: {{salt}} and {{test}} under my user.

When using a CNAME (git.semtamfor.cz) wchich points to my account (sasule) and trying to create an issue I get form which has this code in its action parameter

{code}
#!html
<form id="issue-form" class="aui clearfix"
      action="/sasule/semtamf-r/issues/new"
{code}

If I post an issue it leads me to a dead link page.
